body:
Sends an [HTTP PUT](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Methods/PUT) request to the
specified URL. See [http.put()](atlas/app-services/services/http-actions/http.put) for detailed reference
information, including parameter definitions and return types.

```javascript
exports = async function() {
   const response = await context.http.put({
      url: "https://www.example.com/messages",
      body: { msg: "This is in the body of a PUT request!" },
      encodeBodyAsJSON: true
   })
   // The response body is a BSON.Binary object. Parse it and return.
   return EJSON.parse(response.body.text());
};
```

